# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# EQUITY_AWARD_TYPE → equity_award_basket booleans
# Question: rp_e1 "Which types of equity awards are covered?"
#
# The concept instances describe award types (stock_options, restricted_stock, etc.)
# while entity booleans describe mechanisms (cashless_exercise, tax_withholding,
# net_settlement, clawback, forfeiture). These are orthogonal dimensions.
# No direct 1:1 mapping exists — these concepts remain as Channel 2
# concept_applicability selections. No entity boolean mapping needed.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# SKIPPED: eat_stock_options, eat_restricted_stock, eat_rsus, eat_phantom
# These describe WHAT awards exist, not WHICH mechanisms are permitted.
# The covers_cashless_exercise, covers_tax_withholding, covers_net_settlement,
# covers_clawback, covers_forfeiture booleans are set by separate scalar questions.

